                    "Future forms"
                  ],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "When we talk about future actions and events, we use be going to when we have already decided to do something."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                  "paragraphTitle": null,
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "We use will when we make the decision at the time of speaking."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 4,
                  "paragraphTitle": null,
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "We use the present progressive when we have a planned arrangement at a certain time in the future, usually with another person."
                  ]
                }
